<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-61-1161 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author says the inner workings of the defense policy apparatus, the&quot;Iron Triangle&quot; of the Pentagon, the defense industry and the armed servicesand military appropriations committees in Congress set the prioritiesthat are ultimately reflected in the defense budget. The author explainshow this group decides what weapons will be made, before they are evenon the drawing boards in research and development labs. The defense contractorsinfluence policy and procurement decisions. The Defense Department relieson private industry to supply most of its weapons and the Congressionalcommittees approve the funding. The author says the Iron Triangle mustbe broken.</TEXT></DOC>